They insinuate that they have now no excuse. Pro se quis- que, every one with all possible earnestness. Pro se, pro me, pro te, always mean to the utmost of one’s individual power. Like καθ’ {ava-ov, κατ’ {potat-ro», κατὰ σεαῖἷτον. These words are explained by commentators to signify “alone'' or “with the utmost- exertion.'’ The reason is, that they give only a part of their signification. The words properly mean, to exert one’s power to the utmost, independently of the co-operation of any other.
